  "text": "ETS transcription factors are highly conserved proteins with a unique winged helix-turn-helix DNA-binding domain. These proteins recognize a core 5′-GGA(A/T)-3′ sequence present in downstream target genes. ETS factors activate or repress genes involved in various biological processes, including cellular proliferation, differentiation, transformation, and apoptosis [CITATION_1] .",
